accessibility.text: \"But...anyway, is there anything worse than losing all the memory and waking up alone in a strange grassland? Now that I have nothing to lose, why not have a look?\"
You walk carefully close to the creatures, with clenched fists. Gradually, the jellyfishes seem notice your coming, and start to gather around.
\"It is really not a comfortable experience being surrounded by a flock of strange giant guys.\" You talk to yourself.

After a while, the jellyfish flock suddenly stop gathering around and begin to vibrate much more loudly. You stand in the center of their circle, having a strange but comforting feeling that something seems getting out of your inside part, like a waterflow, directly into the yellow eyes of the jellyfish. It is invisible, but you can strongly feel its moving, flowing, and losing. You want to run away of this, but somehow you cannot move even one step more.
